# Release workflow

When code is ready to ship, follow `docs/LOCAL-DEV.md` § **Release workflow**.

## Agent responsibilities

1. Feature branch only — never commit directly to `master` unless asked.
2. Before PR: `npm run typecheck && npm run lint && npm run build` for non-trivial TS changes.
3. Push branch, `gh pr create --base master`, reply with this **exact handoff layout**:

```markdown
**Compare URL**
https://github.com/comfybear71/same-game-multi/compare/master...BRANCH

**PR Title**
Short imperative title

**PR Description**

## Summary
One paragraph — goal and why.

## Changes
- path/to/file.ts — what changed
- …

## Test plan
- [x] npm run typecheck
- [ ] Vercel: manual step …

PR: #NNN

**Merge instructions**
1. Open Compare URL above (or PR #NNN)
2. Squash and merge
3. Delete branch
4. Sync PC: `git checkout master && git pull origin master && git fetch --prune`

**Release tag**

| Field | Value |
| --- | --- |
| Tag name | `v0.2.N-YYYY-MM-DD` |
| Target | `master` |
| Title | `v0.2.N — One-line summary` |
| Create via | https://github.com/comfybear71/same-game-multi/releases/new?tag=TAG&target=master |

**Release description**

## v0.2.N

### Fixed
- User-facing bullet

### New
- User-facing bullet (if any)
```

- Tag format: `v{major}.{minor}.{patch}-YYYY-MM-DD` (AWST date). Bump patch from latest tag.
- Do **not** push tags or merge PRs unless the user explicitly asks.

## Maintainer (Stuart) on GitHub

Squash merge → delete branch → create Release from handoff tag/title/description.

## After merge — sync PC (not automatic)

Vercel deploys when `master` updates. Deleting the branch does not trigger deploy.

Tell the user to run (or run if asked):

```bash
git checkout master && git pull origin master && git fetch --prune
```

PC matches GitHub only after `git pull`.
